article.description: Brown, Western Michigan beat San Diego 68-66
article.headline: Brown, Western Michigan beat San Diego 68-66
article.linkText: Brown, Western Michigan beat San Diego 68-66
article.story: ANAHEIM, Calif. -- David Brown's layup with 1 second left capped an 8-0 run and lifted Western Michigan over San Diego 68-66 in the Wooden Legacy tournament on Sunday. Brown drove the lane and almost lost control, but recovered and got the shot off. He also hit a jumper with 1:57 left that sparked the Western Michigan run and assisted Connar Tava's layup that tied it at 66-all with 21 seconds left. Brown finished with 14 points, six rebounds and seven assists for Western Michigan (5-2). Tava led the Broncos with 23 points and Tucker Haymond added 10 points and eight rebounds. Christopher Anderson made two free throws to put San Diego (4-3) up 66-60 with 2:08 left but missed two free throws with 7 seconds left with the game tied. Johnny Dee led the Toreros with 17 points, Jito Kok had 15 points and five blocks, Duda Sanadze scored 12 and Anderson 10.
